### ***`<st c="803">`{=html} March 2`</st>`{=html}*** {#007.html_march2}

![Image](ops/images/img01_073.jpg)

*`<st c="811">`{=html} The more closely a person unites with the will of God, the firmer this person becomes in his actions.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="913">`{=html} When a traveler starts on a trip along a road which is under the threat of robbers, he does not go alone. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1020">`{=html}He waits for a friend, someone to be his escort, and then he follows him and so is protected from robbers. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1127">`{=html}A wise man lives his life the same way. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1167">`{=html}But there are so many troubles in this world. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1213">`{=html}How can we stand all of them? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1243">`{=html}What kind of a friend or escort will we find on our way, so that we may pass through our lives without fear? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1352">`{=html}Where should we turn? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1374">`{=html}There is only one answer, only one real friend. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1422">`{=html}That is God.`</st>`{=html}\ `<st c="1434">`{=html} If you follow God everywhere, you will steer clear of trouble. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1498">`{=html}To follow God is to want what He wants, and not to want what He does not want. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1577">`{=html}How to achieve this? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1598">`{=html}You have to understand and follow His laws.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="1641">`{=html} ---After EPICTETUS`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="1658">`{=html} Do not wish for too much, nor think that the things you wish for are the only right or necessary things. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1764">`{=html}You should wish only for those things for which God wishes.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="1823">`{=html} ---HENRI AMIEL`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="1836">`{=html} The right path in life is very narrow, but it is important to find it. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="1908">`{=html}You can understand it, as well as we can understand it, as a walkway of wood built across a swamp; if you step off it, you will plunge into the swamp of misunderstanding and evil. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="2088">`{=html}A wise man returns to the true path at once, but a weak man plunges further and further into the swamp, and it becomes more and more difficult for him to get out.`</st>`{=html}[]{#007.html_page_74}


