`<st c="19186">`{=html} God wants us to fulfill his will here on earth, in our lives. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="19249">`{=html}But life's interests and passions distract us from this every minute. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="19319">`{=html}When we understand this, we can gird ourselves with the physical expression of our attitude to God, prayer.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="19426">`{=html} A personality is a limitation and, therefore, God, as we understand Him, is not a personality. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="19522">`{=html}Prayer is our address to God and yet how can we address one who has no personality? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="19606">`{=html}I address God as if He were a person, though I know it is not so.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="19671">`{=html} A person buried in a deep mine, freezing from the cold in deep ice, dying from hunger alone on the open sea, wasting away in solitude in a prison cell, or simply dying at home, deaf and blind---how could this person live out the remainder of his life if prayer did not exist?`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="19945">`{=html} How good a person feels when, exhausted from striving for goodness in his everyday life, he stretches out his hands to God.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="20069">`{=html} ---BLAISE PASCAL`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="20084">`{=html} One can live without prayer either when he is possessed by his passions or when his life is completely dedicated to God. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="20206">`{=html}But for a person who is fighting his passion and yet far from fulfilling his duty, prayer is a necessary condition of life.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_368}


### ***`<st c="20329">`{=html} December 22`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december22}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="20341">`{=html} Nothing seems to check the notion that the way to improve civilization is affected by changing its outer forms. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="20454">`{=html}This notion is false, and draws the activity of too many people away from effort that truly can improve our lives.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="20568">`{=html} Civilization is first of all a moral thing. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="20613">`{=html}Without truth, respect for duty, love of neighbor, virtue, everything is destroyed. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="20697">`{=html}The morality of a society is alone the basis of civilization.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="20758">`{=html} ---HENRI AMIEL`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="20771">`{=html} The proper direction of man's thought is not toward the creation of new laws for government, but toward the acceptance of every person's moral dignity.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="20923">`{=html} ---EDMUND YATES`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="20937">`{=html} Socialism, when compared with Christianity, is a rather minor, secondary question about the material needs of the working class. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="21067">`{=html}It stands outside the basic questions of human life.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="21119">`{=html} ---FYODOR STRAKHOV`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="21136">`{=html} We should, first of all, understand that we are all children of the same father, and we should fulfill the same general law: live not for ourselves, but to help others be happy.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="21314">`{=html} ---GIUSEPPE MAZZINI`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="21332">`{=html} When we accept false and violent laws and submit to them, we can neither establish truth nor combat lies in this world.`</st>`{=html}*[]{#016.html_page_369}


### ***`<st c="21452">`{=html} December 23`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december23}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="21464">`{=html} Wisdom is understanding how eternal truth can be applied to life.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="21530">`{=html} Socrates was the first who brought philosophy from heaven, distributed it among the people, and enticed them to study the science of life, human morals, and the consequences of good and evil.`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="21722">`{=html} Science is seldom connected with wisdom. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="21764">`{=html}A scholarly person knows many unnecessary things. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="21814">`{=html}A wise person knows few things, but all that he knows is necessary both for humanity and for himself.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="21915">`{=html} He who understands his soul will understand the divine spark within himself.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="21992">`{=html} ---MARCUS TULLIUS CICERO`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22015">`{=html} Wise people cannot be sufficiently educated, and educated people cannot be sufficiently wise.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22109">`{=html} ---LAO-TZU`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22118">`{=html} The goodness given to us by wisdom compares to all other knowledge in the same way that in a desert, a vessel filled with water compares to mountains of gold.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_370}


### ***`<st c="22277">`{=html} December 24`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december24}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="22289">`{=html} Starting from early childhood, as we age we feel the growth of our spiritual power and the diminution of our physical power.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22414">`{=html} Older people who live spiritual lives ever widen their spiritual horizons, and ever expand their consciences. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="22525">`{=html}Older people who live only a daily routine become more and more stupid over the years.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22611">`{=html} ---The T`</st>`{=html}[`<st c="22618">`{=html} ALMUD`</st>`{=html}]{.small}

`<st c="22624">`{=html} One becomes older in order to become kinder; there is no mistake which I have not already made.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22720">`{=html} ---JOHANN WOLFGANG VON GOETHE`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22748">`{=html} The growth and development of the soul is more important than power and glory.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22827">`{=html} ---HENRI AMIEL`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="22840">`{=html} The growth of our physical energy prepares us for spiritual work, for serving God and mankind; this work starts when our body begins to fade away.`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="22987">`{=html} Grow spiritually and help others to do so; it is the meaning of life.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="23057">`{=html} Terrible is the situation of those who cannot perceive spiritual growth in themselves. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="23145">`{=html}They can see only physical life, which will disappear in time.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="23207">`{=html} When you understand your spiritual being and live with it, then instead of despairing you understand the joy that can never be destroyed, which always grows.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_371}


### ***`<st c="23365">`{=html} December 25`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december25}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="23377">`{=html} Kindness and virtue come from the heart, and should be performed without thought for the opinion of others, or of future rewards.`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="23507">`{=html} Virtue and charity start at home. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="23542">`{=html}If you have to go somewhere to display it, then it is not virtue.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="23607">`{=html} Assistance given to the poor by the rich is too often just a gesture of politeness, not real charity.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="23709">`{=html} Charity is good only when it comes as a sacrifice; only then do those who receive the material gift receive the spiritual gift too. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="23842">`{=html}If it is not a sacrifice but a discharge of excess, it can only irritate those who receive it.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_372}


### ***`<st c="23936">`{=html} December 26`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december26}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

*`<st c="23948">`{=html} Childhood is the period in which underlying convictions are formed. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="24017">`{=html}Therefore, the most important part of education is the selection of the things of which a child should be convinced.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="24133">`{=html} Talking and reasoning does not even have one thousandth the influence a true example has. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="24224">`{=html}All lessons about how to behave are worthless when children see the opposite in real life.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="24314">`{=html} What use is it for children when people only speak about goodness, but perform bad deeds in reality?`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="24415">`{=html} ---GUSTAV STRUVE`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="24430">`{=html} The strong desire for a pleasant and ideal life is a child's worst misfortune. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="24510">`{=html}It is crucial that children should know how to work from an early age.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="24580">`{=html} ---IMMANUEL KANT`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="24595">`{=html} It is important to teach children kindness and simplicity in life and work. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="24672">`{=html}All of children's moral and spiritual education should be supported by your own good example. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="24766">`{=html}You should live virtuously, or at least try to do so; the success of your good life will educate your children.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_373}


### ***`<st c="24877">`{=html} December 27`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december27}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="24889">`{=html} All that we see and know does not exist in reality, because it is the product of our limited ability to understand reality.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="25013">`{=html} Instead of saying that the world is reflected in our intellect, better to say that our intellect is reflected in the world.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="25137">`{=html} ---GEORGE LICHTENBERG`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="25157">`{=html} Old fortresses are destroyed, monuments to kings are demolished, old age ravages our bodies. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="25251">`{=html}Only the teachings of kindness are never ruined or affected by age.`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="25318">`{=html} As soon as a person truly looks at himself as only a physical body, then he sees an unsolved puzzle, a contradiction that cannot be unraveled.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="25461">`{=html} In order to understand the true essence of a thing we must transform the physical into the spiritual.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_374}


### ***`<st c="25563">`{=html} December 28`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december28}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="25575">`{=html} Science is vitally important when it is harnessed to reveal the law of human life.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="25658">`{=html} In order to accept the importance of science, we must prove that this activity is useful. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="25749">`{=html}Scientists usually demonstrate that they are doing something and that maybe sometime, someday, this could be useful for people in the future.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="25890">`{=html} The universe is limitless, and impossible for anyone to understand. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="25959">`{=html}Therefore, we cannot completely understand the life of our own body.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="26027">`{=html} ---BLAISE PASCAL`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="26042">`{=html} "Science" is not quite the concept which people use this word to identify; it is the highest, most important, most necessary object of our understanding.`</st>`{=html}*[]{#016.html_page_375}


### ***`<st c="26196">`{=html} December 29`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december29}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

*`<st c="26208">`{=html} As long as there is violence, there will be war. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="26258">`{=html}One cannot defeat violence with more violence, only with nonresistance to and nonparticipation in it.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="26359">`{=html} ---LETURNO`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="26368">`{=html} If my soldiers started thinking, not a single soldier would remain in my army.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="26447">`{=html} ---FREDERICK II`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="26461">`{=html} The wild instinct of military murder has developed in humanity over the course of thousands of years, and has become rooted in our brains. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="26601">`{=html}We must hope that our society will be able to rid itself of this terrible crime.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="26681">`{=html} With time I understand the army code that dictates that a sergeant is always right when he addresses a soldier, that a lieutenant is always right when he addresses a sergeant, and so on up to generals and marshals, even when a person says that two times two equals five. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="26953">`{=html}If you do not obey your superior, you are punished by death, or years in prison.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="27033">`{=html} ---EDWARD EKMAN`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="27047">`{=html} Wars can be stopped only if people are ready to be persecuted for not participating in them. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="27141">`{=html}This is the only way.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_376}


### ***`<st c="27162">`{=html} December 30`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december30}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="27174">`{=html} The understanding of the fraternity and equality of all people becomes more and more popular among mankind.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="27282">`{=html} Do we understand our spiritual fraternity? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="27326">`{=html}Do we understand that we originated from one divine Father whose image we carry in ourselves and for whose perfection we strive? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="27455">`{=html}Have we accepted that there is the same divine life in all people, as well as in ourselves? `</st>`{=html}`<st c="27547">`{=html}And that this makes a natural and free bond among people?`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="27604">`{=html} ---WILLIAM ELLERY CHANNING`</st>`{=html}

*`<st c="27629">`{=html} We can love neither those whom we fear nor those who fear us.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="27691">`{=html} ---MARCUS TULLIUS CICERO`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="27714">`{=html} Family and motherland are but two circles that are part of the wider circle that is humanity. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="27809">`{=html}Those who teach morality and who limit one's duties only to family and country teach a selfishness which is dangerous for all of us.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="27941">`{=html} The understanding of one's unity with all of humanity comes from the understanding of the divine beginning in us all, and gives all our greatest good. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28093">`{=html}True religion creates this understanding, and different prejudices interfere with it---prejudice of state, nation, and class.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_377}


### ***`<st c="28216">`{=html} December 31`</st>`{=html}*** {#016.html_december31}

![Image](ops/images/img01_348.jpg)

`<st c="28228">`{=html} The past does not exist. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28254">`{=html}The future has not begun. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28280">`{=html}The present is an infinitely small point in time in which the already nonexistent past meets the imminent future. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28394">`{=html}At this point, which is timeless, a person's real life exists.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="28456">`{=html} "Time passes by!" we say. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28483">`{=html}Time does not exist; only we move.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="28517">`{=html} ---After the T`</st>`{=html}[`<st c="28530">`{=html} ALMUD`</st>`{=html}]{.small}

*`<st c="28536">`{=html} Time is behind us, time is before us, but in the present there is no time.`</st>`{=html}*

`<st c="28611">`{=html} I consist of spirit and body. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28642">`{=html}Time affects the body, but the life of the spirit has no meaning either in the past or in the future. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28744">`{=html}All its life is concentrated in the present.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="28788">`{=html} ---MARCUS AURELIUS`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="28805">`{=html} Divine spirit is eternal, it exists out of time. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="28855">`{=html}Limitless time and space are divided into small, limited parts to be used by limited beings.`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="28947">`{=html} ---HENRI AMIEL`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="28960">`{=html} The soul is put into our body, so that it can understand the notion of date and time. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="29047">`{=html}It contemplates this fact and calls it "nature."`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="29095">`{=html} ---BLAISE PASCAL`</st>`{=html}

`<st c="29110">`{=html} Time does not exist. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="29132">`{=html}There is only a small and infinite present, and it is only in this present that our life occurs. `</st>`{=html}`<st c="29229">`{=html}Therefore, a person should concentrate all his spiritual force only on this present.`</st>`{=html}[]{#016.html_page_378}

